---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="TurboQuant Study Plan — OpenCastor"
  description="OpenCastor's plan to study and integrate TurboQuant — extreme KV cache compression for local model providers like Ollama, vLLM, and llama.cpp."
  ogUrl="https://opencastor.com/plan"
>

<main>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Research Plan</p>
    <h1 class="reveal reveal-d1">TurboQuant + Local Models</h1>
    <p class="reveal reveal-d2">
      Extreme KV cache compression for Ollama, vLLM, and other local providers.<br>
      Zero accuracy loss. Zero memory overhead. Runs on edge hardware.
    </p>
    <div class="reveal reveal-d3" style="margin-top:1.5rem;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center">
      <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.19874" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="badge" style="background:var(--accent-glow);border:1px solid var(--accent);color:var(--accent);padding:6px 14px;border-radius:20px;font-size:0.8125rem;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none">
        arXiv: 2504.19874
      </a>
      <a href="https://research.google/blog/turboquant-redefining-ai-efficiency-with-extreme-compression/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="badge" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);color:var(--text-secondary);padding:6px 14px;border-radius:20px;font-size:0.8125rem;font-weight:500;text-decoration:none">
        Google Research Blog ↗
      </a>
      <span class="badge" style="background:rgba(45,212,191,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(45,212,191,0.25);color:#2dd4bf;padding:6px 14px;border-radius:20px;font-size:0.8125rem;font-weight:500">
        ICLR 2026
      </span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What is TurboQuant -->
  <section class="container" style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:64px 24px">

    <div class="reveal" style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:16px;padding:32px;margin-bottom:48px">
      <h2 style="font-size:1.25rem;margin:0 0 1rem 0;color:var(--accent)">What is TurboQuant?</h2>
      <p style="margin:0 0 1rem 0;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.7">
        TurboQuant is a Google Research compression algorithm (ICLR 2026) that achieves extreme reduction in KV cache size with <strong style="color:var(--text)">zero accuracy loss and zero memory overhead</strong>. Traditional quantization methods add 1–2 extra bits per value to store quantization constants — TurboQuant eliminates that overhead entirely.
      </p>
      <p style="margin:0;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.7">
        It works in two stages: <strong style="color:var(--text)">PolarQuant</strong> rotates vectors into polar coordinates so normalization overhead disappears, then <strong style="color:var(--text)">QJL (Quantized Johnson-Lindenstrauss)</strong> corrects residual error using just 1 bit per value via a sign-bit transform. Together they compress KV cache entries to as low as 1–2 bits with no perplexity penalty on Gemma and Mistral benchmarks.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Why it matters for edge robots -->
    <div class="reveal" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(220px,1fr));gap:20px;margin-bottom:64px">
      <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:24px">
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;margin-bottom:8px">🧠</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:0.9375rem;margin:0 0 8px 0">Longer context on-device</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;line-height:1.6">8GB RAM robot (Raspberry Pi 5) can hold 4× longer context windows before KV cache eviction. Practical for long task sequences.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:24px">
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;margin-bottom:8px">⚡</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:0.9375rem;margin:0 0 8px 0">Faster token throughput</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;line-height:1.6">Smaller KV cache = faster similarity lookups during attention. Critical for reactive brain latency on Hailo-8 NPU paths.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:24px">
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;margin-bottom:8px">🔒</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:0.9375rem;margin:0 0 8px 0">Fully local, no cloud</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;line-height:1.6">TurboQuant targets inference — not training. Applies to any model already running in Ollama, vLLM, or llama.cpp without retraining.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:24px">
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;margin-bottom:8px">📦</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:0.9375rem;margin:0 0 8px 0">Drop-in for OpenCastor providers</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;line-height:1.6">OpenCastor's provider abstraction layer means TurboQuant can be added as a KV-cache hook without touching model weights or provider APIs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Study phases -->
    <h2 class="reveal" style="font-size:1.5rem;margin:0 0 2rem 0">Study Plan</h2>

    <div class="reveal" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0">

      <!-- Phase 1 -->
      <div style="display:flex;gap:24px;padding-bottom:40px;position:relative">
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;flex-shrink:0">
          <div style="width:40px;height:40px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--accent-glow);border:2px solid var(--accent);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);font-size:0.875rem;flex-shrink:0">1</div>
          <div style="width:2px;flex:1;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);margin-top:8px"></div>
        </div>
        <div style="padding-top:8px">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:8px;flex-wrap:wrap">
            <h3 style="font-size:1.0625rem;margin:0">Algorithm deep-dive</h3>
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--accent);background:var(--accent-glow);border:1px solid var(--accent);padding:2px 10px;border-radius:10px;font-weight:600">Week 1</span>
          </div>
          <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0 0 12px 0;line-height:1.7">Read the TurboQuant, QJL, and PolarQuant papers in full. Implement toy versions of each algorithm in Python to build intuition for distortion bounds and how the sign-bit estimator preserves attention scores.</p>
          <ul style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;padding-left:1.25rem;line-height:1.8;font-size:0.9rem">
            <li>TurboQuant paper — <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.19874" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--accent)">arxiv.org/abs/2504.19874</a></li>
            <li>QJL paper — <a href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1609/aaai.v39i24.34773" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--accent)">AAAI 2025</a></li>
            <li>PolarQuant paper — <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.02617" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--accent)">arxiv.org/abs/2502.02617</a></li>
            <li>Run reference benchmarks: LongBench, Needle-in-Haystack on Gemma 3 locally</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 2 -->
      <div style="display:flex;gap:24px;padding-bottom:40px;position:relative">
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;flex-shrink:0">
          <div style="width:40px;height:40px;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(45,212,191,0.1);border:2px solid #2dd4bf;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:700;color:#2dd4bf;font-size:0.875rem;flex-shrink:0">2</div>
          <div style="width:2px;flex:1;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);margin-top:8px"></div>
        </div>
        <div style="padding-top:8px">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:8px;flex-wrap:wrap">
            <h3 style="font-size:1.0625rem;margin:0">llama.cpp / Ollama integration</h3>
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#2dd4bf;background:rgba(45,212,191,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(45,212,191,0.3);padding:2px 10px;border-radius:10px;font-weight:600">Week 2–3</span>
          </div>
          <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0 0 12px 0;line-height:1.7">Ollama uses llama.cpp under the hood. Study the KV cache layer in llama.cpp (<code style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.85rem">llama_kv_cache</code>) and identify the injection point where PolarQuant/QJL can replace the default FP16 KV store.</p>
          <ul style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;padding-left:1.25rem;line-height:1.8;font-size:0.9rem">
            <li>Map <code style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.85rem">llama_kv_cache_seq_add</code> / <code style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.85rem">llama_decode</code> call graph</li>
            <li>Prototype PolarQuant hook in C++ — replace FP16 → INT4 polar coords on write</li>
            <li>Benchmark: tokens/sec + memory footprint vs baseline on Pi 5 (8GB) and Hailo-8</li>
            <li>Target: Gemma 3 4B at 4-bit KV with zero perplexity regression</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 3 -->
      <div style="display:flex;gap:24px;padding-bottom:40px;position:relative">
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;flex-shrink:0">
          <div style="width:40px;height:40px;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(168,85,247,0.1);border:2px solid rgba(168,85,247,0.7);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:700;color:rgba(168,85,247,0.9);font-size:0.875rem;flex-shrink:0">3</div>
          <div style="width:2px;flex:1;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);margin-top:8px"></div>
        </div>
        <div style="padding-top:8px">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:8px;flex-wrap:wrap">
            <h3 style="font-size:1.0625rem;margin:0">vLLM + OpenAI-compatible API</h3>
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem;color:rgba(168,85,247,0.9);background:rgba(168,85,247,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(168,85,247,0.3);padding:2px 10px;border-radius:10px;font-weight:600">Week 4–5</span>
          </div>
          <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0 0 12px 0;line-height:1.7">vLLM exposes a PagedAttention KV cache via Python. It's the better target for a clean TurboQuant integration — the KV cache blocks map directly to the PolarQuant vector-at-a-time compression model.</p>
          <ul style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;padding-left:1.25rem;line-height:1.8;font-size:0.9rem">
            <li>Study <code style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.85rem">vllm.attention.backends</code> — swap KV block allocator</li>
            <li>Implement <code style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.85rem">TurboQuantKVCache</code> as a vLLM attention backend plugin</li>
            <li>Expose as OpenCastor provider: <code style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.85rem">brain_reactive: vllm/turboquant</code> in RCAN config</li>
            <li>Validate via <code style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.85rem">castor conformance</code> — no regression in planning brain quality gate</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 4 -->
      <div style="display:flex;gap:24px;padding-bottom:40px;position:relative">
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;flex-shrink:0">
          <div style="width:40px;height:40px;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(251,191,36,0.1);border:2px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.5);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:700;color:rgba(251,191,36,0.9);font-size:0.875rem;flex-shrink:0">4</div>
          <div style="width:2px;flex:1;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);margin-top:8px"></div>
        </div>
        <div style="padding-top:8px">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:8px;flex-wrap:wrap">
            <h3 style="font-size:1.0625rem;margin:0">Other local provider support</h3>
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem;color:rgba(251,191,36,0.9);background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.3);padding:2px 10px;border-radius:10px;font-weight:600">Week 6</span>
          </div>
          <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0 0 12px 0;line-height:1.7">Surface TurboQuant across all local provider types in OpenCastor's provider registry via a common <code style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.85rem">kv_compression</code> config key.</p>
          <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr));gap:12px">
            {[
              { name: 'llama.cpp (direct)', status: 'C++ hook', color: 'var(--accent)' },
              { name: 'Ollama', status: 'via llama.cpp', color: 'var(--accent)' },
              { name: 'vLLM', status: 'Python plugin', color: '#2dd4bf' },
              { name: 'LM Studio', status: 'llama.cpp shim', color: 'var(--text-secondary)' },
              { name: 'ExLlamaV2', status: 'CUDA kernel', color: 'var(--text-secondary)' },
              { name: 'mlx-lm (Apple Silicon)', status: 'MLX hook', color: 'var(--text-secondary)' },
            ].map(p => (
              <div style={`display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px`}>
                <span style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:500">{p.name}</span>
                <span style={`font-size:0.75rem;color:${p.color}`}>{p.status}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 5 -->
      <div style="display:flex;gap:24px;padding-bottom:0">
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;flex-shrink:0">
          <div style="width:40px;height:40px;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(34,197,94,0.1);border:2px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.5);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:700;color:rgba(34,197,94,0.9);font-size:0.875rem;flex-shrink:0">5</div>
        </div>
        <div style="padding-top:8px">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:8px;flex-wrap:wrap">
            <h3 style="font-size:1.0625rem;margin:0">OpenCastor provider config + RCAN telemetry</h3>
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem;color:rgba(34,197,94,0.9);background:rgba(34,197,94,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.3);padding:2px 10px;border-radius:10px;font-weight:600">Week 7–8</span>
          </div>
          <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0 0 16px 0;line-height:1.7">Ship as a first-class OpenCastor feature. Robots report KV compression ratio and token throughput improvement in RCAN telemetry.</p>
          <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.3);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:10px;padding:20px;font-family:monospace;font-size:0.8125rem;line-height:1.8;color:#a5f3fc">
            <span style="color:#6b7280"># bob.rcan.yaml — proposed config</span><br/>
            <span style="color:#f0abfc">brain_reactive</span>: <span style="color:#86efac">ollama/gemma3:4b</span><br/>
            <span style="color:#f0abfc">brain_planning</span>: <span style="color:#86efac">anthropic/claude-opus-4-6</span><br/>
            <span style="color:#f0abfc">kv_compression</span>:<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#f0abfc">method</span>: <span style="color:#86efac">turboquant</span><br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#f0abfc">bits</span>: <span style="color:#fbbf24">2</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#6b7280"># 1–4 bit KV cache</span><br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#f0abfc">polar_quant</span>: <span style="color:#fbbf24">true</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#6b7280"># zero overhead normalization</span><br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#f0abfc">qjl_residual</span>: <span style="color:#fbbf24">true</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#6b7280"># 1-bit sign correction</span><br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#f0abfc">backend</span>: <span style="color:#86efac">auto</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#6b7280"># detect llama.cpp or vLLM</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Bob is the right test bed -->
  <section class="alt-section" style="padding:64px 0">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px">
      <h2 class="reveal" style="font-size:1.4rem;margin:0 0 1.5rem 0">Why Bob (RRN-000000000001) is the right test bed</h2>
      <div class="reveal" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:16px">
        <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:20px">
          <div style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:6px">Hailo-8 NPU</div>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;line-height:1.6">26 TOPS on-chip. TurboQuant's INT2 KV cache fits the Hailo tensor memory model. Potential for hardware-accelerated PolarQuant rotation.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:20px">
          <div style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:6px">Pi 5 — 8GB RAM</div>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;line-height:1.6">Memory-constrained edge device. TurboQuant's 4× compression directly translates to 4× longer context windows — measurable in OpenCastor's thought log.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:20px">
          <div style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:6px">Dual-brain: VLA + Claude</div>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;line-height:1.6">The reactive brain (openvla-7b via Ollama) is exactly the use case TurboQuant targets — long task sequences, tight memory, zero tolerance for quality regression.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:20px">
          <div style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:6px">RCAN v2.2 telemetry</div>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0;line-height:1.6">KV compression metrics (ratio, throughput delta, cache hit rate) can be reported back via RCAN STATUS messages and the <code style="font-size:0.8rem">/api/conformance</code> endpoint.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="container" style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;padding:64px 24px 96px;text-align:center">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Contribute</p>
    <h2 class="reveal reveal-d1" style="font-size:1.75rem;margin:0 0 1rem 0">Follow the research</h2>
    <p class="reveal reveal-d2" style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin:0 0 2rem 0;line-height:1.7">
      Implementation notes and benchmark results will be published in the OpenCastor docs and GitHub discussions as each phase completes.
    </p>
    <div class="reveal reveal-d3" style="display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap">
      <a href="https://github.com/craigm26/OpenCastor/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-primary">
        GitHub Discussions →
      </a>
      <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.19874" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-secondary">
        Read the Paper
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

</BaseLayout>
